<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I would just like to comment that the Trueshot Longbow is NOT Magic - it can not hit magic beings like the Runed Oak or the Raincaller!</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Japirna Longtalon</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>1999-11-24 11:24:18</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I have to agree with the first comment, it definitely is not magic.<BR>
<BR>
BUT, besides that, this is a MUST bow for a Ranger.  Unless you can get a Runed Oak Bow(rare drop on a level 35 mob), or a 2-Cam Darkwood Bow(sell around 500 - 600pp), you should definitely get a Trueshot.  If you are a skilled fletcher, and have a skill around 130-140+ you can definitely fletch one of these after doing the quest.  If you decided to not take the fletching route, then you can still buy one much cheaper than the Darkwood of Runed Oak.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
