<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Knapweed</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>1999-12-08 14:28:34</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I have read many comments about how you need a fletching skill of approximately 140 to make this bow. I made one first time at a skill of 68 after completing the quest.<BR>
<BR>
I know of many others who made their FIRST bow with similar or even lower skill. However, the point is that this was their FIRST bow. After this, they certainly needed a skill of 130 plus to be able to make any subsequent bows.<BR>
<BR>
Most of the people I have met who consider that a high skill is needed haven't even tried at a lower skill as they are afraid of failure.<BR>
<BR>
My advice is, 'Give it a crack' and post your findings here.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Sedari</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-10 04:00:00</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I made my first trueshot yesterday, with a fletching skill of 106 and wisdom at 82. I gathered materials enough for 7 tries and succeded on the 4th try.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Woodstalk Buzzardbait</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-10 14:35:37</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I, too, made my Trueshot with a Fletching skill of around 106.  Successful on my second try.  )  <BR>
<BR>
The following may be regarded as spoiler information, so read on at your own mental risk.  No one ever told me that you need about two of everything for each attempt.  1 spiderling silk, 1 truant wood, 1 microserver (no drop), 1 dwarven wire goes into the box to get the truant wood bow staff. THEN 1 bow staff, 1 dwarven wire, 1 planing tool (30pp to me) and one microserver goes into the fletching kit to attempt the bow.  <BR>
<BR>
Also, since the bow staff is no drop, you can't have more than one, so you can't make a bunch.  To be ready to make multiple attempts, have everything else ready in quantity, and just tell what-his-name "I will gather the material" so he gives you the box.  Give it back to get the staff, make the attempt.  If it doesn't work, tell him again and get another box.<BR>
<BR>
And for those who are as brain dead as I am:  Once you make the bow, subsequent failures do NOT mean you lack the skill.  IT IS LORE!! YOU CAN ONLY HOLD ONE AT A TIME!!!  <BR>
<BR>
Fortunately , when you fail, you get the 30pp planing tool back.  It only took me 5 attempts (after my success) to figure out what was going on.  hee hee. That was after learning you needed two of most of the parts for each attempt and making the circuit gathering 10 of everything (which allowed 5 more attempts).<BR>
<BR>
Also, you get the Kiola nuts for about 8 gp (figure 1pp so you don't run short of money) at the Inn on the Island you stop at on the way from Freeport.  If you are fast, you can run off the boat, go in the door, turn left immediately and buy about 20 and quickly run back to the boat before it leaves.  Don't forget to buy some water flasks to go with them.  They are for sale at a vendor when you get off the boat, or up by the entrance to Kaladim if you forget.<BR>
<BR>
20 nuts and flasks will get you 20 Trumpy tonics which result in 10 Dwarven wires for 5 attempts at the bow.<BR>
<BR>
Since I came from Surefall, I found it easier to buy some small lamps and give them to Kyle or Lyle (upstairs in the Hog Heaven Inn or whatever in W Freeport) for the Truant wood on the way thru Freeport instead of getting it last.<BR>
<BR>
For the same 5 attempts, don't forget to gather 10 microservers in Steamfont.  Spiderling silk (only need 5 for 5 attempts) is also available in Steamfont, but I found a vendor in Kaladim area selling them, too.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this isn't too much info.<BR>
<BR>
Woodstalk Buzzardbait, L24/25/24/25/24/25 Ranger. Brell</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kelador</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-11 10:33:21</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Quick comment on the first comment... no bow can hit a magic mob - not even Rain Caller (unless you decide to use one of it's charges).  Only magic arrows can hit magic mobs - currently only summoned arrows can do this although fletched magic arrows are now available on the test server and will be introduced soon on the live servers.<BR>
<BR>
You folks who made the Trueshot with about 100 skill or less are lucky - I made my first one at 151 on my 8th or 9th attempt.  Initially there was no skill minimum on the Trueshot then the quest was changed to introduce Maesyn's speech about needing to be a Master fletcher to make it.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
